value.value: Anticuerpos positivos anti-perilipina-1
The presence of autoantibodies in the serum that react against perilipin-1 (PLIN1).
Calcificación esplénica

definition.value: Calcification, that is, pathological deposition of calcium salts in the spleen.

value.value: Esófago corto
Abnormal reduction in the length of the esophagus.

definition.value: The short esophagus was defined by surgeons as the inability to reduce the gastroesophageal (GE) junction below the diaphragm during surgery, due to inadequate esophageal mobilization. Short esophagus was also defined by endoscopists when the GE junction is positioned in adults at a distance less than 40 cm from the mouth (normal value is approximately 45 cm).

value.value: Perforación gástrica
A full-thickness injury of the wall of the stomach.
Vólvulo gástrico
A gastric volvulus occurs when the stomach rotates on itself at least 180 degrees along its transverse or longitudinal axis.

definition.value: Gastric strangulation is a complication that can occur after the development of acute gastric volvulus.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de CD163 soluble en sangre
The concentration of Soluble CD163 in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

definition.value: Soluble CD163 is considered to be a marker of alternatively activated (anti-inflammatory) macrophages.

value.value: Prueba positiva de aglutininas frías
Cold agglutinin are erythrocyte antibodies which possess the property of agglutinating red blood cells at temperatures of below 37 degrees C, this phenomenon is reversible after heating.
Anticuerpos positivos anti-DL
The presence of Donath-Landsteiner (D-L) autoantibodies (immunoglobulins) in the serum.

definition.value: This feature may be observed in paroxysmal cold haemoglobinuria.

value.value: Autoanticuerpos positivos antieritrocitos

definition.value: The presence of an antibody in the blood circulation that is directed against an antigen on the surface of erythrocytes (red-blood cells).

value.value: Sustancia reductora no glucosa en la orina

Abnormal result for this screening test for urinary reducing substances including glucose, fructose, galactose, lactose, pentose and maltose, as well as amino acids, cysteine, tyrosine, homogentisic acid, ketone bodies, ascorbic acid and many drugs. This term is applied if the urine stick test for glucose was negative (normal).

definition.value: Detection of reducing substances in urine has been a standard laboratory procedure for about 50 yr. It is used as a screening test for inborn errors of carbohydrate metabolism. Although the test has poor specificity and most states perform mandatory newborn screening for the common genetic defects, most clinical laboratories still perform this as a reflex test on all pediatric urine samples.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de ribósido de succinilaminoimidazol carboxamida en orina

label.value: Elevated urinary succinylaminoimidazole carboxamide riboside level

value.value: Presence of succinylaminoimidazole carboxamide riboside (SAICAr). SAICAr is a toxic intermediate metabolite of purine synthesis.
Aumento del nivel de ácido hialurónico en orina

definition.value: Excessive amount of hyaluronic acid in urine.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de metilmalonilcarnitina en orina

definition.value: The amount of methylmalonylcarnitine in the urine, normalized for urine concentration, is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Aumento del nivel de ácido trihidroxicolestanoico en orina

definition.value: Presence of trihydroxycholestanoic acid in the urine. Trihydroxycholestanoic acid is an intermediate in the biosynthesis of cholic acid. Elevated plasma levels of trihydroxycholestanoic acid have been found in patients with Zellweger syndrome.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de amoníaco en el líquido cefalorraquídeo

definition.value: The concentration of amonia in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Prueba positiva de VDRL en líquido cefalorraquídeo
An abnormal (positive) result of the Venereal Disease Research Laboratory (VDRL) test performed in cerebrospinal fluid (CSF), suggesting past or present neurosyphilis.
Aumento de la concentración de ácido guanidinoacético en el líquido cefalorraquídeo
The concentration of guanidinoacetic acid in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.
Bandas de inmunoglobulina G oligoclonal en líquido cefalorraquídeo

Oligoclonal immunoglobulin G (IgG) bands (OCBs) are a useful diagnostic tool to detect a central humoral response. In particular, cerebrospinal fluid (CSF)-restricted OCBs represent a hallmark of multiple sclerosis (MS).
Disminución de la concentración de 3-metoxi-4-hidroxifenilglicolaldehído en el líquido cefalorraquídeo
The concentration of 3-methoxy-4-hydroxyphenylglycolaldehyde in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is below the lower limit of normal.
Aumento de la concentración de cadena B de alfa-cristalina en líquido cefalorraquídeo

label.value: Elevated CSF alpha-crystallin B chain concentration

definition.value: The concentration of alpha-crystallin B chain in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is above the upper limit of normal.

value.value: Disminución de la concentración de creatina en el líquido cefalorraquídeo

definition.value: The concentration of creatine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Disminución de la concentración de proteína Z en sangre

definition.value: The concentration of protein Z in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.
The vitamin K-dependent protein Z is encoded by the PROZ gene (HGNC:9460).

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de 27-hidroxicolesterol en sangre
The concentration of 27-hydroxycholesterol in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

definition.value: 27-hydroxycholesterol is a primary metabolite of cholesterol.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de lisofosfatidilcolina en sangre
The concentration of lysophosphatidylcholines in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.
Disminución de la concentración del factor de crecimiento similar a la insulina 2 en sangre

label.value: Reduced circulating insulin-like growth factor 2 concentration

definition.value: The concentration of insulin-like growth factor 2 (IGF2) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal. IGF2 is a peptide hormone regulating various cellular processes such as proliferation and apoptosis.

label.value: Decreased circulating nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide concentration

value.value: Disminución de la concentración de nicotinamida adenina dinucleótido en sangre

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Decreased circulating nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide concentration

definition.value: The concentration of nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

label.value: Diminished circulating reduced nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NADH) concentration

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Diminished circulating reduced nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NADH) concentration

definition.value: The concentration of reduced nicotinamide adenine dinucleotide (NADH) in the blood circulation is below the lower limit of normal.

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: Elevated circulating fibroblast growth factor 23 concentration

label.value: Elevated circulating fibroblast growth factor 23 concentration

value.value: The concentration of fibroblast growth factor 23 in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.

definition.value: Fibroblast growth factor-23 (FGF23) is a bone-derived hormone suppressing phosphate reabsorption and vitamin D hormone synthesis in the kidney.

value.value: Disminución de la concentración de asparagina en el líquido cefalorraquídeo

definition.value: The concentration of asparagine in the cerebrospinal fluid (CSF) is below the lower limit of normal.

value.value: Masa pancreática

definition.value: A swelling or enlargement localized to the pancreas. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

value.value: Masa en el intestino delgado

definition.value: A swelling or enlargement localized to the small intestine. The word mass is usually used at an early stage of the diagnostic workup before the precise nature of the swelling has been determined.

value.value: Compresión del nervio facial

definition.value: Impingement of another object such as a blood vessel upon the facial nerve, causing it to lose volume in the compressed region.

value.value: Defecto de perfusión pulmonar

Lack of blood perfusion in a specific area of the lung. Pulmonary ventilation (V) and Perfusion (Q) scan, also known as lung V/Q scan, is a nuclear test that uses the perfusion scan to delineate the blood flow distribution and the ventilation scan to measure airflow distribution in the lungs.
Orificio ureteral ectópico

Drainage of the ureter on one or both sides into an abnormal location. Normally the ureter drains via the internal ureteral orifice at the trigone of the urinary bladder. Ectopic ureteral orifice can be either intravesical (bladder neck) or, more often, extravesical. Ectopia in women is more frequently found in the urethra and the vaginal vestibule; much less frequently in vagina and in uterus. In men it is mostly found in the posterior urethra; in the male genital tract is very rare.
Duplicación de cuello uterino
A congenital developmental defect characterized by the presence of two cervices on the uterus.
Lipoma espinal intradural

Intradural spinal lipoma (ISL) constitutes approximately 1% of all spinal tumors and is usually associated with lumbo-sacral spinal dysraphism. ISLs unassociated with spinal dysraphism are rare with only a few cases being reported in literature. They are seen in children and young adults and are situated on the posterior aspect of the spinal cord in the cervico-thoracic or thoracic regions. They represent intradural, subpial, juxtamedullary lesions.
Lesión cerebelosa hiperintensa T2

definition.value: A lighter than expected T2 signal on magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) of the cerebellum. This term refers to a localized hyperintensity affecting a particular region of the cerebellum.

value.value: Obstrucción de la vena cava inferior
Physical invasion or compression of the inferior vena cava by a pathological process or by thrombosis within the vein itself.

definition.value: Inferior vena cava syndrome (IVCS) iis a sequence of signs and symptoms that refers to obstruction or compression of the inferior vena cava (IVC). Symptoms and signs of IVCS result from a reduced venous return to the heart, as well as a pooling of blood in the IVC, which causes hypotension, tachycardia, lower extremity edema, elevated liver enzymes, end-organ failures and, hypoxia, altered mental status, and death. IVCS is less frequently found in comparison with the superior vena cava syndrome.

value.value: Nódulo reumatoide

definition.value: A well-demarcated, flesh colored, subcutaneous and usually freely movable lump or mass. Rheumatoid nodules can vary in size from small, pea sized lesions up to the size of a lemon and are most often round. The nodules usually are doughy or firm however and not tender. Typically rheumatoid nodules are distributed over areas of repeated trauma or pressure and occur adjacent to joints on extensor surfaces, such as the elbow, fingers and forearms.

value.value: Aumento de la concentración de proinsulina en sangre
The concentration of proinsulin in the blood circulation is above the upper limit of normal.
Sensación de ardor en los ojos

definition.value: A feeling of stinging or irritation of the eyes.

value.value: Collarettes en las pestañas

definition.value: Buildup of waxy flesh-colored scales on the margin of the eyelid.

value.value: Ampolla en la membrana timpánica

Presence of blisters (bullae) on the tympanic membrane, often accompanied by fever, thickening, and erythematous appearance of the tympanic membrane, decreased or absent light reflex, and decreased mobility.
Distribución localizada en la barba y bigote.

definition.value: Applies to an abnormality whose distribution and appearance are located at regions of the male face covered by a beard or mustache.

value.value: Kerión

Kerion is an erythematous, boggy, tender, often sterile, weeping nodule or plaque with pustules and draining sinuses. Hair in these areas appears lusterless, brittle, and is easily plucked. Kerion can be solitary or multiple but is usually unilateral. Patients with inflammatory tinea barbae may have constitutional symptoms like fever and malaise. Kerion is a coalesced sterile pustule, but occasionally they can get superinfected with cutaneous bacteria and develop regional lymphadenopathy.
Localización troncal

definition.value: Applies to an abnormality that is situated in (or predominant in) the trunk of the body. The trunk is the main part of a person's body, not including the head, legs, or arms.

Disminución de la actividad de la alquil-dihidroxiacetonafosfato sintasa en fibroblastos cultivados

value.value: Activity of alkyl-dihydroxyacetonephosphate (DHAP) synthase below the lower limit of normal in cultured fibroblasts.
Depósitos glomerulares de fibronectina
Accumulation of fibronectin in the glomerulus.

definition.value: Fibronectin glomerulopathy (FNG) is characterized by extensive deposition of fibronectin in the glomeruli, especially in the mesangial and subendothelial regions.

value.value: Cariomegalia tubular renal
Marked enlargement of nuclei observed predominantly in the proximal convoluted tubule cells.
